вҠў correct
  given translateвҶ’spanish-text вүЎ "Cell es un lenguaje metacircular auto-bootstrapping para LLMs. Los programas son documentos. La ejecuciГіn completa los valores. El documento ES el programa ES el estado. Las celdas comienzan como lenguaje natural (soft) y progresivamente se cristalizan en cГіdigo determinista (hard) bajo presiГіn de oracle. Cell es el Scheme de los LLMs."
  given diffвҶ’drifted-segments вүЎ [
    {original: "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language for LLMs.", back: "Cell is a metacircular auto-bootstrapping language for LLMs.", drift: "Term 'self-bootstrapping' replaced with 'auto-bootstrapping' and word order changed."},
    {original: "Execution fills in values.", back: "Execution completes the values.", drift: "Verb 'fills in' replaced with 'completes'. Loses the blank-filling metaphor."}
  ]
  given diffвҶ’acceptable вүЎ false
  given sourceвҶ’text вүЎ "Cell is a self-bootstrapping metacircular language for LLMs. Programs are documents. Execution fills in values. The document IS the program IS the state. Cells start as natural language (soft) and progressively crystallize into deterministic code (hard) under oracle pressure. Cell is the Scheme of LLMs."
  yield corrected-spanish, changed-count

  вҲҙ For each segment in В«diffвҶ’drifted-segmentsВ», retranslate ONLY that
    segment from В«sourceвҶ’textВ» into Spanish, replacing the corresponding
    segment in В«translateвҶ’spanish-textВ». Preserve segments that did NOT
    drift. Set changed-count to the number of segments replaced.

